- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the impact of AI-enabled intelligent assistants on team behaviors and performance, which has implications for the societal and ethical considerations of AI deployment. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on the interaction between humans and AI-enabled intelligent assistants in collaborative settings. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper discusses the deployment of AI-enabled intelligent assistants and their impact on team performance. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves analyzing the behavioral data of teams in a lab experiment, which may involve computational complexity considerations. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve information retrieval techniques to analyze the behavioral data collected from the lab experiment.
